PrecisOrder setting aside the election of NORMAN COPENACE JR. as chief of the OJIBWAYS OF ONEGAMING BAND OF INDIANS in Ontario as well as the election of four other individuals who were elected to the office of Councillor at an election held by that band on December 18, 1992, due to a violation of subsections 75(1) and 77(1) of the Indian Act which might have affected the results of the voting.
Attachments
precis:
Order setting aside the election of NORMAN COPENACE JR. as chief of the
OJIBWAYS OF ONEGAMING BAND OF INDIANS in Ontario as well as the election
of four other individuals who were elected to the office of Councillor at
an election held by that band on December 18, 1992, due to a violation of
subsections 75(1) and 77(1) of the Indian Act which might have affected the
results of the voting.
